<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY WILLIAM DICKEY</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 6 to 8 servings </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1 (5-pound) bag Yukon gold potatoes, cut into 1-inch chucks </p><p class="no-indent">1 (8-ounce) package cream cheese, softened </p><p class="no-indent">½ cup butter, softened </p><p class="no-indent">3 tablespoons minced fresh chives </p><p class="no-indent">2 tablespoons minced fresh dill </p><p class="no-indent">1 teaspoon salt </p><p class="no-indent">½ teaspoon ground black pepper </p><p class="no-indent">1 cup sour cream</p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 13x9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. In a large Dutch oven, add potatoes and enough water to cover. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat; reduce heat, and simmer for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Drain well. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">3. Add cream cheese and butter to hot potatoes. Let stand, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Add chives, dill, salt, and pepper. Using a potato masher, mash potatoes to desired consistency. Stir in sour cream. Spoon mixture into prepared pan. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">4. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned.</p></div>
